Something like
````rs
mod m {
    pub trait Hello {
        fn hello() {}
    }
    pub trait World {
        fn world() {}
    }
}

pub use m::Hello as _;
pub use m::World as _;
````
creates documentation listing two traits called "`_`"

![Screenshot_325](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3986214/147618149-ef5a0529-c52e-44de-8e71-c6aef18e4391.png)

both of which link to *the same* URL `.../target/doc/crate_name/trait._.html` and which contains documentation for one of the two traits, chosen seemingly at random.

When I add a few implementations, sometimes (not very reproducably) I've even gotten a weirdly broken page. E.g. I sometimes get
````rs
mod m {
    pub trait Hello {
        fn hello() {}
    }

    pub trait World {
        fn world() {}
    }

    impl World for u8 {
        fn world() {}
    }

    impl World for u16 {
        fn world() {}
    }

    impl World for u32 {
        fn world() {}
    }
}

pub use m::Hello as _;
pub use m::World as _;
````
to generate a page that looks like this

![Screenshot_326](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3986214/147618429-f888264d-0039-43c3-b4f0-19ed1eba4f24.png)

